**The bug is `word-break: break-all`** which is set in `medium-editor.css` at line 209!

This `word-break: break-all` property causes ALL text to break at ANY character position, not just at word boundaries. This is why:
- Normal words like "My", "likeness", "childish", "the", "born", "state", "bleak", "also", "Abraham", "dark", "scattered", "intact" etc. are all being broken mid-word.
- The long test word `superlongwordthatshouldonlybreakappropriately` also breaks at arbitrary positions.

The correct behavior should be:
- `word-break: break-word` or `overflow-wrap: break-word` - which breaks long words that would overflow, but keeps normal-length words intact at word boundaries.
- OR `word-break: normal` (default) with `overflow-wrap: break-word` for the long word case.

